    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1317"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1317">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/79b.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Miller</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following message was sent to George C. Carothers at Torreon to-day: [Here
                    follows telegram to Special Agent Carothers, May 16, 1914.]</p>
                <pb facs="0892" n="776" xml:id="pg_776"/>
                <p>For fear communication may be interrupted between General Carranza and Tampico
                    authorities above telegram is repeated to you. Please call upon the
                    Constitutionalist Commander in authority at Tampico and communicate substance of
                    this telegram. If he has not received instructions from General Carranza since
                    the General received the above telegram, insist on delay until he hears from the
                    General. It is important that nothing shall be done at Tampico that can give
                    just cause for complaint from foreign residents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
